<subSubSection id="1610B24B084A224214BA3F88D5A39B5A" pageId="0" pageNumber="185" type="description">
<paragraph id="9DE9E50856FD894D41ABCF82BA0E5F56" pageId="0" pageNumber="185">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="860DF96534CBD1D8F6A4A77C9ACEC542" pageId="0" pageNumber="185">
<emphasis id="A2625EBBAAFEF6E27BEDF91B94EC46CC" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="185">Female</emphasis>
(Fig. 
<figureCitation id="1A7092B73B02E76BE187C846FC7BF29B" captionStart="Figures 1–10" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figures 1 - 10. Paraleptomenes setaceus sp. nov. Holotype (♀): 1, 3, 5, 7, 9, 10 paratype (♂): 2, 4, 6, 8. 1, 2 habitus (dorsal view) 3, 4 head (frontal view) 5 vertex and part of pronotum (dorsal view) 6 A 6 - A 13 7 mesosoma (dorsal view) 8 metasoma (ventral view) 9 tegula (dorsal view) 10 mesosoma (lateral view)." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.90.82546.figures1-10" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/677827" pageId="0" pageNumber="185">1</figureCitation>
). Body length 6.3 mm, forewing length 5.7 mm; black, with the following parts orange-yellow: base of mandible, two lateral complete bands along margins of clypeus, longitudinal interantennal spot, scape ventrally, a small spot of ocular sinus, a line behind eye at gena, an anterior interrupted band of pronotum, tegula (except brownish red at middle), parategula, metanotum, apices of fore and mid femora, fore and mid tibiae (slightly dark ventrally) and tarsi (slightly dark apically), apex of hind tibia, hind tarsus, apical bands of T1-T2, and S2 (broader on T2); wings transparent brown, fore wing with an apical dark spot.
</paragraph>
<caption id="30DF4F996A5C1C1BACE4E4DFB16CD101" doi="10.3897/jhr.90.82546.figures1-10" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/677827" pageId="0" pageNumber="185" start="Figures 1–10" startId="F1">
<paragraph id="0AECC4053F3D86775C09A9298FB972C4" pageId="0" pageNumber="185">
<emphasis id="4E24D37B6913B85F4EEC623BAC7D6D26" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="185">Figures 1-10.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="65EDD00E8A7E9514D28A534A4777BEA2" authorityName="Bai, Chen &amp; Li" authorityYear="2022" class="Insecta" family="Vespidae" genus="Paraleptomenes" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Paraleptomenes setaceus" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="185" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="setaceus">
<emphasis id="7B1F610968A18A19A834333F6553EF94" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="185">Paraleptomenes setaceus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. nov. Holotype (♀): 
<emphasis id="BA35174890317CC53186563B9041A39C" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="185">1, 3, 5, 7, 9, 10</emphasis>
paratype (♂): 
<emphasis id="E7421C6DB6400E553F9C59EA4D5A35EE" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="185">2, 4, 6, 8</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="04EB3209C6099A8EED7776A361BBCF1E" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="185">1, 2</emphasis>
habitus (dorsal view) 
<emphasis id="7B8A08A6C43A0EFD6755FDF8CFA1FA14" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="185">3, 4</emphasis>
head (frontal view) 
<emphasis id="891661AFA14DD5F2F62A43899ED9C0B8" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="185">5</emphasis>
vertex and part of pronotum (dorsal view) 
<emphasis id="81000D3D875B05D35ACE6353D9C6FA21" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="185">6</emphasis>
A6-A13 
<emphasis id="4A7B528E62F9BE1CDEF6061EDFBC26C6" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="185">7</emphasis>
mesosoma (dorsal view) 
<emphasis id="8FF684E8A62B11F8C7C4F879B9B31E24" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="185">8</emphasis>
metasoma (ventral view) 
<emphasis id="F6A835F9629E4188BE04CBECE0D00697" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="185">9</emphasis>
tegula (dorsal view) 
<emphasis id="E172CDF27EBE4C2D70664548B051AD61" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="185">10</emphasis>
mesosoma (lateral view).
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="B67450F7F75717772C410E408ECD5A17" pageId="0" pageNumber="185">
<emphasis id="5B18C0A3D5D77F8E69C1FBBCB4DEA5E9" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="185">
<emphasis id="9E81D7A7C15EA73050823D8159A0B490" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="185">Head</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
Clypeus (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="9689D4E0D731C6A009EFF726F7A469C4" captionStart="Figures 1–10" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figures 1 - 10. Paraleptomenes setaceus sp. nov. Holotype (♀): 1, 3, 5, 7, 9, 10 paratype (♂): 2, 4, 6, 8. 1, 2 habitus (dorsal view) 3, 4 head (frontal view) 5 vertex and part of pronotum (dorsal view) 6 A 6 - A 13 7 mesosoma (dorsal view) 8 metasoma (ventral view) 9 tegula (dorsal view) 10 mesosoma (lateral view)." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.90.82546.figures1-10" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/677827" pageId="0" pageNumber="185">3</figureCitation>
) about 1.0 times as wide as long, flat in the middle part, indistinctly with lateral longitudinal raised carina from middle to apex, with extremely fine sparse punctures, and punctures at apex larger and deeper, or even longitudinally striate, apical margin somewhat emarginated, clypeal width about 3.1 times its apical width; distance between inner eye margins at vertex about 1.2 times of the distance between inner eye margins at clypeus; interantennal space slightly raised; frons and vertex with dense punctures, punctures sparser than 
<taxonomicName id="CD4F2C00F7ECC9B4FF04AECFC51A4EB2" class="Insecta" genus="P." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="P. darugiriensis" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="185" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="darugiriensis">
<emphasis id="87C7AA56C5468A1B4EFB157D4F35DB85" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="185">P. darugiriensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Fig. 
<figureCitation id="0AC49456A99E1A26C0A9086168548984" captionStart="Figures 1–10" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figures 1 - 10. Paraleptomenes setaceus sp. nov. Holotype (♀): 1, 3, 5, 7, 9, 10 paratype (♂): 2, 4, 6, 8. 1, 2 habitus (dorsal view) 3, 4 head (frontal view) 5 vertex and part of pronotum (dorsal view) 6 A 6 - A 13 7 mesosoma (dorsal view) 8 metasoma (ventral view) 9 tegula (dorsal view) 10 mesosoma (lateral view)." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.90.82546.figures1-10" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/677827" pageId="0" pageNumber="185">3</figureCitation>
); posterior area of hind ocelli with a row of short longitudinal carina along occipital carina in the middle area, occipital carina dorsally not sinuate as 
<taxonomicName id="ED072AE188F6033089C0ABFC714F9339" class="Insecta" genus="P." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="P. darugiriensis" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="185" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="darugiriensis">
<emphasis id="81ACD7BE207771C307427BFDFC26CDF1" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="185">P. darugiriensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Fig. 
<figureCitation id="E3E00937D721249623461B773FEC54F2" captionStart="Figures 1–10" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figures 1 - 10. Paraleptomenes setaceus sp. nov. Holotype (♀): 1, 3, 5, 7, 9, 10 paratype (♂): 2, 4, 6, 8. 1, 2 habitus (dorsal view) 3, 4 head (frontal view) 5 vertex and part of pronotum (dorsal view) 6 A 6 - A 13 7 mesosoma (dorsal view) 8 metasoma (ventral view) 9 tegula (dorsal view) 10 mesosoma (lateral view)." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.90.82546.figures1-10" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/677827" pageId="0" pageNumber="185">5</figureCitation>
); distance between posterior ocellus about equal to the distance from posterior ocellus to inner eye margin; punctures of gena sparser than vertex.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="411C04F616ADB2C1DDF0C422EAA50895" pageId="0" pageNumber="185">
<emphasis id="DC28C804237913C814BC97A934A73506" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="185">
<emphasis id="A4F1D58D7B7EDC5588660B59576C5CBB" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="185">Mesosoma</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
Pronotum coarsely, densely punctate and reticulate, except the middle area, anterior face without obviously depressed fovea in the middle, with dense punctures and somewhat reticulate on both sides, pronotal transverse carina weak, especially absent in the middle (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="37359B686477EB9E5900BB02E9E0799A" captionStart="Figures 1–10" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figures 1 - 10. Paraleptomenes setaceus sp. nov. Holotype (♀): 1, 3, 5, 7, 9, 10 paratype (♂): 2, 4, 6, 8. 1, 2 habitus (dorsal view) 3, 4 head (frontal view) 5 vertex and part of pronotum (dorsal view) 6 A 6 - A 13 7 mesosoma (dorsal view) 8 metasoma (ventral view) 9 tegula (dorsal view) 10 mesosoma (lateral view)." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.90.82546.figures1-10" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/677827" pageId="0" pageNumber="185">5</figureCitation>
); mesoscutum with dense punctures, interspaces reticulate, with two longitudinal furrows of punctures on apical margin (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="8FAB011709910E882F4824CD2A067658" captionStart="Figures 1–10" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figures 1 - 10. Paraleptomenes setaceus sp. nov. Holotype (♀): 1, 3, 5, 7, 9, 10 paratype (♂): 2, 4, 6, 8. 1, 2 habitus (dorsal view) 3, 4 head (frontal view) 5 vertex and part of pronotum (dorsal view) 6 A 6 - A 13 7 mesosoma (dorsal view) 8 metasoma (ventral view) 9 tegula (dorsal view) 10 mesosoma (lateral view)." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.90.82546.figures1-10" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/677827" pageId="0" pageNumber="185">7</figureCitation>
); scutellum convex in lateral view (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="F8CD34D17A96815DAAF246FE7B345E04" captionStart="Figures 1–10" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figures 1 - 10. Paraleptomenes setaceus sp. nov. Holotype (♀): 1, 3, 5, 7, 9, 10 paratype (♂): 2, 4, 6, 8. 1, 2 habitus (dorsal view) 3, 4 head (frontal view) 5 vertex and part of pronotum (dorsal view) 6 A 6 - A 13 7 mesosoma (dorsal view) 8 metasoma (ventral view) 9 tegula (dorsal view) 10 mesosoma (lateral view)." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.90.82546.figures1-10" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/677827" pageId="0" pageNumber="185">10</figureCitation>
), with dense punctures, interspaces reticulate; metanotum weakly convex, sloping down to apical margin, with dense punctures, and apical margin leathery; mesopleuron posterodorsally with obviously raised blunt teeth (Figs 
<figureCitation id="4BD13F28AB4EB4A4475D66C821C6160C" captionStart="Figures 1–10" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figures 1 - 10. Paraleptomenes setaceus sp. nov. Holotype (♀): 1, 3, 5, 7, 9, 10 paratype (♂): 2, 4, 6, 8. 1, 2 habitus (dorsal view) 3, 4 head (frontal view) 5 vertex and part of pronotum (dorsal view) 6 A 6 - A 13 7 mesosoma (dorsal view) 8 metasoma (ventral view) 9 tegula (dorsal view) 10 mesosoma (lateral view)." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.90.82546.figures1-10" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/677827" pageId="0" pageNumber="185">9</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="FE7BAD01E826F300C897429CBF62041E" captionStart="Figures 1–10" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figures 1 - 10. Paraleptomenes setaceus sp. nov. Holotype (♀): 1, 3, 5, 7, 9, 10 paratype (♂): 2, 4, 6, 8. 1, 2 habitus (dorsal view) 3, 4 head (frontal view) 5 vertex and part of pronotum (dorsal view) 6 A 6 - A 13 7 mesosoma (dorsal view) 8 metasoma (ventral view) 9 tegula (dorsal view) 10 mesosoma (lateral view)." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.90.82546.figures1-10" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/677827" pageId="0" pageNumber="185">10</figureCitation>
), punctures mostly similar to pronotum, posteroventrally with fine sparser punctures; metapleuron smooth, sparsely punctate, punctures smaller than other parts of mesosoma; propodeum dorsally with large and deep flat-bottomed punctures, interspaces carinate and reticulate, the boundary between dorsal and posterior surfaces not obvious, punctures on lateral surface dense, interspaces carinate and reticulate, shallower than other parts of mesosoma except metapleuron; posterior surface obviously depressed, margin with dense and shallow punctures, and medially smooth and without punctures, with short oblique striae along median carina on both sides, median carina about 0.8 times of the length of whole propodeum.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="1AB30F041353A733EAB6159A953BF6B5" pageId="0" pageNumber="185">
<emphasis id="291E24B163FB0A897DEA1D1A1BEE043E" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="185">
<emphasis id="4C1E48BD4F1BF56651BFC46912DBDA0F" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="185">Metasoma</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
Leathery, punctures smaller than head and mesosoma; T1 about 1.9 times as wide as long, narrower than T2, punctures on anterior inclined surface sparse, punctures on dorsal surface dense, without punctures at the end, slightly concave near the end (Figs 
<figureCitation id="44FA1B6CB84164B0527C3628C32321BB" captionStart="Figures 1–10" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figures 1 - 10. Paraleptomenes setaceus sp. nov. Holotype (♀): 1, 3, 5, 7, 9, 10 paratype (♂): 2, 4, 6, 8. 1, 2 habitus (dorsal view) 3, 4 head (frontal view) 5 vertex and part of pronotum (dorsal view) 6 A 6 - A 13 7 mesosoma (dorsal view) 8 metasoma (ventral view) 9 tegula (dorsal view) 10 mesosoma (lateral view)." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.90.82546.figures1-10" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/677827" pageId="0" pageNumber="185">1-2</figureCitation>
); T2 about 1.2 times as wide as long, with sparse punctures at base and then punctures gradually denser and larger near the apical margin, and with thin apical lamella; S2 with sparse punctures in the middle, those laterally and apically denser, larger than the base of T2, and with thin apical lamella; T3-T5 with dense punctures; metasomal segment 6 almost without punctures.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E10E770686400848039FD5FFD49E3862" pageId="0" pageNumber="185">
<emphasis id="594C719E3E76D7DF12D01084BD80710D" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="185">Male</emphasis>
(Fig. 
<figureCitation id="82658EC157633CC416D9028587798049" captionStart="Figures 1–10" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figures 1 - 10. Paraleptomenes setaceus sp. nov. Holotype (♀): 1, 3, 5, 7, 9, 10 paratype (♂): 2, 4, 6, 8. 1, 2 habitus (dorsal view) 3, 4 head (frontal view) 5 vertex and part of pronotum (dorsal view) 6 A 6 - A 13 7 mesosoma (dorsal view) 8 metasoma (ventral view) 9 tegula (dorsal view) 10 mesosoma (lateral view)." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.90.82546.figures1-10" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/677827" pageId="0" pageNumber="185">2</figureCitation>
). Body length 5.8 mm, forewing length 5.5 mm. Sculpture, punctuation, setae, and coloration as in female except as follows: clypeus (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="48664AD58983D886AE7CB41A5F837C76" captionStart="Figures 1–10" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figures 1 - 10. Paraleptomenes setaceus sp. nov. Holotype (♀): 1, 3, 5, 7, 9, 10 paratype (♂): 2, 4, 6, 8. 1, 2 habitus (dorsal view) 3, 4 head (frontal view) 5 vertex and part of pronotum (dorsal view) 6 A 6 - A 13 7 mesosoma (dorsal view) 8 metasoma (ventral view) 9 tegula (dorsal view) 10 mesosoma (lateral view)." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.90.82546.figures1-10" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/677827" pageId="0" pageNumber="185">4</figureCitation>
) yellow except outer margin, with thick white setae, clypeus about 1.2 times as wide as long, apical margin medially deeply emarginate, transparent, laterally forming a sharp tooth, clypeal width about 3.4 times as wide as that of emargination, emargination about 2.7 times as wide as long; distance between inner eye margins at vertex about 1.6 times of the distance between inner eye margins at clypeus; A13 about 1.6 times as long as basal width, small, slender, finger-like and edge almost straight, backward not reaching the base of A11 (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="D4A8D93383C251851B2E073427BA138C" captionStart="Figures 1–10" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figures 1 - 10. Paraleptomenes setaceus sp. nov. Holotype (♀): 1, 3, 5, 7, 9, 10 paratype (♂): 2, 4, 6, 8. 1, 2 habitus (dorsal view) 3, 4 head (frontal view) 5 vertex and part of pronotum (dorsal view) 6 A 6 - A 13 7 mesosoma (dorsal view) 8 metasoma (ventral view) 9 tegula (dorsal view) 10 mesosoma (lateral view)." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.90.82546.figures1-10" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/677827" pageId="0" pageNumber="185">6</figureCitation>
); punctures of frons sparser (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="E94C453A0EFFD7C4241404860CDA344C" captionStart="Figures 1–10" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figures 1 - 10. Paraleptomenes setaceus sp. nov. Holotype (♀): 1, 3, 5, 7, 9, 10 paratype (♂): 2, 4, 6, 8. 1, 2 habitus (dorsal view) 3, 4 head (frontal view) 5 vertex and part of pronotum (dorsal view) 6 A 6 - A 13 7 mesosoma (dorsal view) 8 metasoma (ventral view) 9 tegula (dorsal view) 10 mesosoma (lateral view)." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.90.82546.figures1-10" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/677827" pageId="0" pageNumber="185">4</figureCitation>
); front of mid and hind coxae yellow; metasomal segment 6 with fine sparse punctures; S7 with fine punctures and basally with a row of thick brown setae (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="71BB25FCDA6245A685CAE4FCF3506E12" captionStart="Figures 1–10" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figures 1 - 10. Paraleptomenes setaceus sp. nov. Holotype (♀): 1, 3, 5, 7, 9, 10 paratype (♂): 2, 4, 6, 8. 1, 2 habitus (dorsal view) 3, 4 head (frontal view) 5 vertex and part of pronotum (dorsal view) 6 A 6 - A 13 7 mesosoma (dorsal view) 8 metasoma (ventral view) 9 tegula (dorsal view) 10 mesosoma (lateral view)." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.90.82546.figures1-10" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/677827" pageId="0" pageNumber="185">8</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="03D2BB38E08FD95E73D0111D69F8B7CF" pageId="0" pageNumber="185" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="11AC99B893E98537B8AA531BB2EE23D9" pageId="0" pageNumber="185">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D848045CC674BE0FD1FFA3595D0F4392" pageId="0" pageNumber="185">China (Yunnan).</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="AB71AE5690168094FE544AAEDB16A317" pageId="0" pageNumber="185" type="remarks">
<paragraph id="1B9EEA674C32FF2C923390C27F6BD27F" pageId="0" pageNumber="185">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="96BC3A2625E40B9512C5D02E460DE75A" pageId="0" pageNumber="185">
This species resembles 
<taxonomicName id="F7C3929A7744218B12AE5FE887A78ACF" class="Insecta" genus="P." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="P. transfoveolus" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="185" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="transfoveolus">
<emphasis id="9114C7959062D89C8440954DE0373E69" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="185">P. transfoveolus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. nov. with the character of mesopleuron posterodorsally with obviously raised blunt teeth (Figs 
<figureCitation id="D79DE0C0AAC438E9FC8294F5F953578E" captionStart="Figures 1–10" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figures 1 - 10. Paraleptomenes setaceus sp. nov. Holotype (♀): 1, 3, 5, 7, 9, 10 paratype (♂): 2, 4, 6, 8. 1, 2 habitus (dorsal view) 3, 4 head (frontal view) 5 vertex and part of pronotum (dorsal view) 6 A 6 - A 13 7 mesosoma (dorsal view) 8 metasoma (ventral view) 9 tegula (dorsal view) 10 mesosoma (lateral view)." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.90.82546.figures1-10" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/677827" pageId="0" pageNumber="185">9</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="BF8EF548237422D79A574DC8F22612FA" captionStart="Figures 11–19" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figures 11 - 19. Paraleptomenes transfoveolus sp. nov. Holotype (♀) 11, 13, 15, 16, 18, 19 paratype (♂) 12, 14, 17. 11, 12 habitus (dorsal view) 13, 14 head (frontal view) 15 mesosoma (dorsal view) 16 vertex and part of pronotum (dorsal view) 17 A 5 - A 13 18 tegula (dorsal view) 19 mesosoma (lateral view)." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.90.82546.figures11-19" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/677828" pageId="0" pageNumber="185">18</figureCitation>
), and resembles 
<taxonomicName id="B7EE46A671D835D8F3A859211376494D" class="Insecta" genus="P." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="P. communis" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="185" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="communis">
<emphasis id="6F11D8E9ABD80AA840F2CF99BD87F644" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="185">P. communis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with the character of male A13 small, slender, finger-like and almost straight, narrowed at the apex (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="DB89B174FA9F72B2DAE1D45422BEBA70" captionStart="Figures 1–10" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figures 1 - 10. Paraleptomenes setaceus sp. nov. Holotype (♀): 1, 3, 5, 7, 9, 10 paratype (♂): 2, 4, 6, 8. 1, 2 habitus (dorsal view) 3, 4 head (frontal view) 5 vertex and part of pronotum (dorsal view) 6 A 6 - A 13 7 mesosoma (dorsal view) 8 metasoma (ventral view) 9 tegula (dorsal view) 10 mesosoma (lateral view)." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.90.82546.figures1-10" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/677827" pageId="0" pageNumber="185">6</figureCitation>
). It differs from the related species and all other members of the genus by the following character combination: female clypeus with indistinct lateral longitudinal raised carina from middle to apex (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="4556625FD0762BE556D38A1AE067ACD8" captionStart="Figures 1–10" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figures 1 - 10. Paraleptomenes setaceus sp. nov. Holotype (♀): 1, 3, 5, 7, 9, 10 paratype (♂): 2, 4, 6, 8. 1, 2 habitus (dorsal view) 3, 4 head (frontal view) 5 vertex and part of pronotum (dorsal view) 6 A 6 - A 13 7 mesosoma (dorsal view) 8 metasoma (ventral view) 9 tegula (dorsal view) 10 mesosoma (lateral view)." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.90.82546.figures1-10" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/677827" pageId="0" pageNumber="185">3</figureCitation>
), anterior face of pronotum in female without obviously depressed foveae in the middle (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="52CDF6EFF2782F8BCE0286F4084189F2" captionStart="Figures 1–10" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figures 1 - 10. Paraleptomenes setaceus sp. nov. Holotype (♀): 1, 3, 5, 7, 9, 10 paratype (♂): 2, 4, 6, 8. 1, 2 habitus (dorsal view) 3, 4 head (frontal view) 5 vertex and part of pronotum (dorsal view) 6 A 6 - A 13 7 mesosoma (dorsal view) 8 metasoma (ventral view) 9 tegula (dorsal view) 10 mesosoma (lateral view)." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.90.82546.figures1-10" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/677827" pageId="0" pageNumber="185">5</figureCitation>
); A13 of the male small, slender, finger-like and lateral edge almost straight, backward reaching near the base of A11 (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="C9439E1273EFD35863D9CFA26EB8B0D4" captionStart="Figures 1–10" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figures 1 - 10. Paraleptomenes setaceus sp. nov. Holotype (♀): 1, 3, 5, 7, 9, 10 paratype (♂): 2, 4, 6, 8. 1, 2 habitus (dorsal view) 3, 4 head (frontal view) 5 vertex and part of pronotum (dorsal view) 6 A 6 - A 13 7 mesosoma (dorsal view) 8 metasoma (ventral view) 9 tegula (dorsal view) 10 mesosoma (lateral view)." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.90.82546.figures1-10" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/677827" pageId="0" pageNumber="185">6</figureCitation>
), punctures of frons sparser (Figs 
<figureCitation id="84E45A4E070A4BA1EA27C31633D6DA95" captionStart="Figures 1–10" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figures 1 - 10. Paraleptomenes setaceus sp. nov. Holotype (♀): 1, 3, 5, 7, 9, 10 paratype (♂): 2, 4, 6, 8. 1, 2 habitus (dorsal view) 3, 4 head (frontal view) 5 vertex and part of pronotum (dorsal view) 6 A 6 - A 13 7 mesosoma (dorsal view) 8 metasoma (ventral view) 9 tegula (dorsal view) 10 mesosoma (lateral view)." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.90.82546.figures1-10" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/677827" pageId="0" pageNumber="185">3-4</figureCitation>
), mesopleuron posterodorsally with obviously raised blunt teeth (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="F4B8EAE45A3792A0B9062941B6D42EBF" captionStart="Figures 1–10" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figures 1 - 10. Paraleptomenes setaceus sp. nov. Holotype (♀): 1, 3, 5, 7, 9, 10 paratype (♂): 2, 4, 6, 8. 1, 2 habitus (dorsal view) 3, 4 head (frontal view) 5 vertex and part of pronotum (dorsal view) 6 A 6 - A 13 7 mesosoma (dorsal view) 8 metasoma (ventral view) 9 tegula (dorsal view) 10 mesosoma (lateral view)." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.90.82546.figures1-10" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/677827" pageId="0" pageNumber="185">9</figureCitation>
) and S7 basally with a row of thick brown setae (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="F3D41DE40BB7D771C19D1536F790219D" captionStart="Figures 1–10" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figures 1 - 10. Paraleptomenes setaceus sp. nov. Holotype (♀): 1, 3, 5, 7, 9, 10 paratype (♂): 2, 4, 6, 8. 1, 2 habitus (dorsal view) 3, 4 head (frontal view) 5 vertex and part of pronotum (dorsal view) 6 A 6 - A 13 7 mesosoma (dorsal view) 8 metasoma (ventral view) 9 tegula (dorsal view) 10 mesosoma (lateral view)." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.90.82546.figures1-10" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/677827" pageId="0" pageNumber="185">8</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="453F88BC233FD664C673A6BD4FB2BDA6" pageId="0" pageNumber="185" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="743F0C19779A5577A40A52D407BE266D" pageId="0" pageNumber="185">Etymology.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="9EE797076499C1145CDC1DB4EE5DB8E5" pageId="0" pageNumber="185">
The specific name 
<emphasis id="BD3C54BEBBC38E712C131C56C29129E3" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="185">setaceus</emphasis>
is derived from Latin word: 
<emphasis id="4B40CF83E8A09A2B3A81A697F3AB6924" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="185">setace</emphasis>
(= with hair), referring to the base of S7 with a row of thick brown setae.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
</treatment>
